  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nLightClientIniter assumes the finalized state is in the cache. That's a big strech and will break in long non-finality\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/6cf7c2c3f3df6012bd4ce773ab3b5310c347e884/packages/lodestar/src/chain/lightClient/LightClientIniter.ts#L97\r\n\r\nIntead, store all checkpoints, or all checkpoints after N slots (i.e. 32) to guard against short lived forks. Then store by checkpoint (epoch | block-root) in reverse for fast pruning and update the init proof route to have the full checkpoint as parameter\r\n\r\n",
